data.name: Turkey Burger
data.quickTastyDescription: A juicy turkey burger seasoned to perfection, served on a toasted bun with fresh toppings.
detailedCookingInstructions: In a mixing bowl, combine ground turkey, salt, pepper, garlic powder, and onion powder. Mix well.
Form the mixture into 4 equal patties.
Preheat a skillet or grill over medium heat and cook the patties for about 6-7 minutes on each side or until they reach an internal temperature of 165°F (74°C).
During the last minute of cooking, place a slice of cheddar cheese on each patty to melt.
Toast the burger buns on the grill or in a toaster.
Assemble the burgers by placing the turkey patty on the bun and adding lettuce, tomato, ketchup, and mustard to taste.
data.modifiersForBase: Add toppings like avocado or bacon for extra flavor.
